700009f-a.text:
2756 to 2752 Third Ave. (extreme right), at, adjacent and south of the S.E. corner of East 146th Street. Also shown, prominently, is the 146th Street side of the corner house, No. 2756.

About 1914.
James Suydam.

700120f-a.text:
E. 146th Street, adjoining the southwest corner of Third Avenue, showing the Mott Haven Reformed Dutch Church and parish house. The parish house, a two-story brick house, was formerly the Bronson Catholic Club.

P.L. Sperr
April 28, 1941

700114f-b.text:
(1) East 145th Street, north side, west from Third Avenue to College Avenue, the Street making a sharp bend to the left near College
Avenue. Note the 146th Street Mission.
April 29, 1941
(2) Numbers 345-347 East 146th Street, adjoining the Mission, which can be seen on the right and set back from the building line about one hundred feet. In the background is Public School No. 18 on Courtlandt Avenue.
P. L. Sperr  April 29, 1941
No Reproductions
